1. FEATURES
-----------

- Create `.rawdist` packages from a directory with a `rawdist.conf`
- Automatic SHA256 checksums generation and verification
- Fetch packages from URLs with local caching
- Install packages to configurable target directories (template support)
- Remove packages and clean up install directories
- Manifest file to track installed packages
- Lock file for reproducible resolution (name/version/source/checksum)
- File filtering with glob patterns (include/exclude)
- Abstract filesystem trait for testability (mock filesystem)
- Rich error types with diagnostic codes and help texts (via `miette`)
- Atomic file writes (tmp + rename) with file locking (via `fs2`)
- Path traversal protection during extraction
- Validation of `rawdist.conf` according to strict rules
- Designed as a library – easy to build a CLI on top


2. INSTALLATION
---------------

2.1 Add to Cargo.toml
    Since the crate is not published on crates.io yet, add it as a git
    dependency:

        [dependencies]
        librawdist = { git = "https://github.com/mroczect/librawdist.git" }

    Or specify a tag:

        librawdist = { git = "https://github.com/mroczect/librawdist.git", tag = "v0.3.2" }

2.2 Build from source
    Requirements: Rust (edition 2021+), Git.

        git clone https://github.com/mroczect/librawdist.git
        cd librawdist
        cargo build --release

    The library will be compiled and can be used by other projects via
    path dependency:

        [dependencies]
        librawdist = { path = "../librawdist" }


3. QUICK START
--------------

    use librawdist::{
        create_package,
        RawdistConfig,
        fs::RealFs,
    };

    fn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
        let fs = RealFs;
        let config = RawdistConfig::load_from_dir(std::path::Path::new("my_theme"))?;
        create_package(
            &fs,
            std::path::Path::new("my_theme"),
            std::path::Path::new("my_theme.rawdist"),
            &config,
        )?;
        println!("Package created.");
        Ok(())
    }

    For more detailed usage, see section 4.6 and 9.


4. LIBRARY USAGE (RUST API)
----------------------------

4.1 Modules overview
    The library exposes these public modules:

        librawdist::checksum   – hash generation, formatting, parsing
        librawdist::error      – error types (RawdistError)
        librawdist::fetch      – download .rawdist from URL
        librawdist::filter     – glob include/exclude logic
        librawdist::fs         – filesystem trait and RealFs implementation
        librawdist::install    – install and remove packages
        librawdist::lock       – lock file structures and operations
        librawdist::manifest   – manifest load/save
        librawdist::package    – create, extract, and move packages
        librawdist::types      – configuration and manifest data types
        librawdist::verify     – verify a package's integrity

    Re‑exported items (convenience):

        - librawdist::RawdistError
        - librawdist::fetch_package
        - librawdist::install_package
        - librawdist::remove_package
        - librawdist::create_package
        - librawdist::extract_to_temp
        - librawdist::move_extracted
        - librawdist::verify_package
        - librawdist::RawdistConfig

4.2 Key types

    4.2.1 RawdistConfig
        The top‑level configuration deserialized from `rawdist.conf`.
        Fields:
            package   : PackageMeta
            rawssg    : RawssgReqs (default: minimal)
            files     : FilePatterns (default: include all)
            install   : InstallConfig
            metadata  : toml::value::Table (arbitrary extra data)

        Methods:
            validate() -> Result<(), RawdistError>
                Checks package name, version, target_dir safety, etc.
            load_from_dir(dir: &Path) -> Result<Self, RawdistError>
                Reads `rawdist.conf` from a directory and validates it.

    4.2.2 PackageMeta
        Metadata describing the package.
        Fields:
            name            : String
            version         : String (semver)
            description     : Option<String>
            authors         : Option<Vec<String>>
            license         : Option<String>
            repository      : Option<String>
            homepage        : Option<String>
            documentation   : Option<String>
            keywords        : Option<Vec<String>>
            categories      : Option<Vec<String>>
            release_date    : Option<String>

    4.2.3 RawssgReqs
        Requirements for the Rawssg runtime.
        Fields:
            min_version   : Option<String>
            max_version   : Option<String>
            r#type        : String (default "theme")

    4.2.4 FilePatterns
        Inclusion and exclusion patterns (glob syntax).
        Fields:
            include   : Vec<String>  (default ["**/*"])
            exclude   : Vec<String>

    4.2.5 InstallConfig
        Installation parameters.
        Fields:
            target_dir    : String   (default "themes/{{ package.name }}")
            merge_config  : Option<String> (optional path relative to target)

    4.2.6 InstalledPackage
        Record of an installed package.
        Fields:
            name            : String
            version         : String
            install_path    : PathBuf (absolute)
            config_merged   : Option<String>

    4.2.7 Manifest
        Manifest.toml (or similar) containing installed packages.
        Fields:
            packages : Vec<InstalledPackage>

        Implements Default (empty manifest).

    4.2.8 LockFile / LockEntry
        Lock file for reproducible installations.
        LockEntry fields: name, version, source, checksum.
        LockFile { packages: Vec<LockEntry> }
        Methods:
            load(path) -> Result<LockFile, RawdistError>
            save(path) -> Result<(), RawdistError>
            add_package(&mut self, name, version, source, checksum)

        Both Load/Save use file locks and atomic rename.

    4.2.9 RawdistError
        Comprehensive error enum with `thiserror` and `miette` derive.
        Variants:
            Io(std::io::Error)
            Config(String)
            TomlParse { path, source }
            ChecksumMismatch { path }
            MissingFile { path }
            Manifest(String)
            NotInstalled(String)
            WalkDir(walkdir::Error)
            InvalidInput(String)
            Validation(String)
            VersionMismatch { name, required, current }
            PathTraversal(PathBuf)
            Network(String)

        Each variant includes a diagnostic code and, where appropriate,
        a help message.

    4.2.10 FileSystem (trait)
        Trait abstracting filesystem operations for testability.
        Methods:
            read_to_string, read, write, create_dir_all, remove_dir_all,
            exists, is_dir, is_file, read_dir, copy_file, rename,
            canonicalize, walk_dir.

        The standard implementation is `RealFs`, which delegates to
        `std::fs`. Users can provide mock implementations for testing.

4.3 Public functions

    4.3.1 fetch_package(url: &str, dest_path: Option<&Path>) -> Result<PathBuf, RawdistError>
        Downloads a `.rawdist` file from a URL.
        If `dest_path` is None, saves to `$CACHE_DIR/librawdist/cache/`
        using the filename from the URL. Returns the path to the
        downloaded file.

    4.3.2 create_package(fs: &dyn FileSystem, src_dir: &Path, output_path: &Path, config: &RawdistConfig) -> Result<(), RawdistError>
        Creates a `.rawdist` archive from a source directory.
        Steps:
            1. Generate checksums of all matching files (include/exclude).
            2. Append those files into a tar.gz archive.
            3. Add `checksums.sha256` to the archive.
            4. Compress and write to `output_path`.

    4.3.3 extract_to_temp(fs: &dyn FileSystem, archive_path: &Path) -> Result<PathBuf, RawdistError>
        Extracts a `.rawdist` archive into a temporary directory,
        verifies every file against the embedded `checksums.sha256`,
        then removes the checksum file and returns the path to the
        extracted directory (kept alive – not auto‑deleted).
        Aborts on checksum mismatch or missing files.

    4.3.4 move_extracted(src: &Path, target: &Path) -> Result<(), RawdistError>
        Renames the extracted directory to the final target directory.
        Fails if target already exists.

    4.3.5 install_package(archive_path: &Path, target_override: Option<&Path>, manifest_path: &Path) -> Result<(), RawdistError>
        Full installation routine:
            1. Validate that the file has `.rawdist` extension.
            2. Extract to temp and verify.
            3. Load `rawdist.conf` from the extracted directory.
            4. Resolve target directory (override or from config template).
            5. Reject if target already exists.
            6. Move extracted content to target.
            7. Update the manifest file (add/replace entry).
        Returns `Ok(())` on success.

    4.3.6 remove_package(package_name: &str, manifest_path: &Path) -> Result<(), RawdistError>
        Removes an installed package:
            1. Load manifest.
            2. Find package by name (error if not found).
            3. Remove its install directory (warns if missing).
            4. Save updated manifest.

    4.3.7 verify_package(archive_path: &Path) -> Result<(), RawdistError>
        Verifies a `.rawdist` archive by extracting to temp and
        validating all checksums. The temporary directory is deleted
        afterwards. Returns Ok if all checks pass.

4.4 Checksum utilities
    Functions in `librawdist::checksum`:

        hash_file(fs: &dyn FileSystem, path: &Path) -> Result<String, RawdistError>
            Reads a file and returns its SHA256 hex string.

        generate_checksums(fs, root, patterns) -> Result<BTreeMap<PathBuf, String>>
            Walks root, filters files, and hashes them. Ensures
            `rawdist.conf` is included.

        format_checksums(&BTreeMap) -> String
            Produces the `hash  path` format used in `checksums.sha256`.

        parse_checksums(content: &str) -> Result<BTreeMap<PathBuf, String>>
            Parses the checksum file. Accepts both two‑space and single‑space
            separators.

4.5 Filter utilities
    librawdist::filter::is_included(rel_path, includes, excludes) -> bool
        Returns true if the relative path matches any include pattern
        (glob) and is not excluded by any exclude pattern. Exclude takes
        priority.

4.6 Integration example
    A complete workflow: download, verify, install, then remove.

        use librawdist::{
            fetch_package,
            verify_package,
            install_package,
            remove_package,
            RawdistError,
        };
        use std::path::Path;

        fn main() -> Result<(), RawdistError> {
            let manifest_path = Path::new("rawdist-manifest.toml");

            // 1. Download
            let archive = fetch_package(
                "https://example.org/packages/my-theme.rawdist",
                None,
            )?;

            // 2. Verify (optional, install also verifies)
            verify_package(&archive)?;

            // 3. Install
            install_package(&archive, None, manifest_path)?;

            // 4. Later, remove
            remove_package("my-theme", manifest_path)?;

            Ok(())
        }


5. CONFIGURATION (rawdist.conf)
-------------------------------

5.1 Format
    A file named `rawdist.conf` placed in the root of the package source.
    It must be valid TOML. Example:

        [package]
        name = "my-theme"
        version = "1.0.0"
        description = "A beautiful theme"
        authors = ["Author Name <email@example.com>"]
        license = "MIT"
        repository = "https://github.com/user/repo"

        [rawssg]
        min_version = "0.5.0"
        type = "theme"

        [files]
        include = ["layouts/**/*", "assets/**/*", "rawdist.conf"]
        exclude = ["*.log", "tmp/**"]

        [install]
        target_dir = "themes/{{ package.name }}"
        merge_config = "user.conf"

        [metadata]
        custom_key = "value"

5.2 Fields detail
    - package.name          : must be alphanumeric, '-' or '_' only.
    - package.version       : must be valid semver (e.g. "1.2.3").
    - rawssg.min_version    : optional, minimum Rawssg version.
    - rawssg.max_version    : optional, maximum compatible version.
    - rawssg.type           : package type (default "theme").
    - files.include         : list of glob patterns to include. Default `["**/*"]`.
    - files.exclude         : list of glob patterns to exclude. Exclude overrides include.
    - install.target_dir    : relative path, may contain `{{ package.name }}` placeholder.
    - install.merge_config  : optional file to merge into existing configs.
    - metadata              : free‑form TOML table.

5.3 Validation rules
    The method `RawdistConfig::validate()` enforces:
        - package name is not empty and only contains allowed characters.
        - version parses as a valid semver.
        - target_dir does not start with `/` and does not contain `..`.
        - files.include is not empty.
        - merge_config (if present) is relative and safe.
    Violations result in `RawdistError::Validation` with a descriptive message.


6. PACKAGE FORMAT (.rawdist)
----------------------------

6.1 Internal structure
    A `.rawdist` file is a gzip‑compressed tar archive containing:
        - All files matching the include/exclude patterns,
          preserving their relative paths from the source root.
        - A file named `checksums.sha256` at the root of the archive.

    The checksums file contains the SHA256 hash and path of every file
    in the archive, in the format `hash  path\n`. It is generated
    automatically by `create_package` and used by `extract_to_temp`
    to verify integrity.

6.2 checksums.sha256 format
    One entry per line, hash and relative path separated by two spaces.
    Example:

        e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855  rawdist.conf
        8f2e5...  layouts/default.html

    Both two‑space and single‑space separators are accepted during parsing.

6.3 Security: path traversal prevention
    During extraction, every entry path is checked for `..` components.
    Additionally, the canonical destination of each file is compared
    against the canonical extraction root. Any attempt to write outside
    the root triggers `RawdistError::PathTraversal`.


7. MANIFEST AND LOCK FILES
--------------------------

7.1 Manifest (installed packages)
    A TOML file (typically `rawdist-manifest.toml`) tracking currently
    installed packages. Maintained by `install_package` and `remove_package`.

    Structure:
        [[packages]]
        name = "my-theme"
        version = "1.0.0"
        install_path = "/absolute/path/to/themes/my-theme"
        config_merged = "user.conf"

    The manifest is read with file locking (shared) and written atomically
    (exclusive lock, tmp file, rename). If the file does not exist, an
    empty manifest is assumed.

7.2 Lock file (pinned versions)
    Optional lock file (e.g., `rawdist.lock`) for reproducible environments.
    Each entry records:
        name, version, source URL, checksum (SHA256 of the .rawdist file).

    Structure:
        [[packages]]
        name = "my-theme"
        version = "1.0.0"
        source = "https://.../my-theme.rawdist"
        checksum = "abc123..."

    Loaded/saved via `lock::LockFile::load` and `save`, with the same
    atomic‑write and locking pattern. The method `add_package` replaces
    an existing entry with the same name.


8. ERROR HANDLING
-----------------

All fallible functions return `Result<T, RawdistError>`. The error enum
provides rich diagnostics when used with `miette` (e.g., in a CLI):

    Error: Checksum verification failed for file layouts/broken.html
      Diagnostic code: librawdist::checksum_mismatch
      Help: The package may be corrupted or tampered. Download again from official source.

When using the library programmatically, you can match on the error
variants:

    match err {
        RawdistError::ChecksumMismatch { path } => { ... },
        RawdistError::MissingFile { path } => { ... },
        ...
    }

I/O and walkdir errors are transparently wrapped. Network errors are
captured as `RawdistError::Network`.


9. EXAMPLES
-----------

9.1 Building a package
    use librawdist::fs::RealFs;
    use librawdist::types::RawdistConfig;
    use librawdist::create_package;

    fn main() -> Result<(), librawdist::RawdistError> {
        let fs = RealFs;
        let src = std::path::Path::new("my_theme");
        let config = RawdistConfig::load_from_dir(src)?;
        create_package(&fs, src, std::path::Path::new("my_theme.rawdist"), &config)?;
        Ok(())
    }

9.2 Installing a package
    use librawdist::{fetch_package, install_package};

    fn main() -> Result<(), librawdist::RawdistError> {
        let archive = fetch_package("https://example.org/packages/my_theme.rawdist", None)?;
        install_package(&archive, None, std::path::Path::new("rawdist-manifest.toml"))?;
        Ok(())
    }

9.3 Removing a package
    use librawdist::remove_package;

    fn main() -> Result<(), librawdist::RawdistError> {
        remove_package("my_theme", std::path::Path::new("rawdist-manifest.toml"))?;
        Ok(())
    }

9.4 Verifying a package
    use librawdist::verify_package;

    fn main() -> Result<(), librawdist::RawdistError> {
        verify_package(std::path::Path::new("downloaded.rawdist"))?;
        println!("Package is intact.");
        Ok(())
    }


10. CONTRIBUTING
----------------

Contributions are welcome! Please open issues or pull requests on the
GitHub repository. Before submitting:
    - Ensure the code compiles without warnings.
    - Existing tests pass (cargo test).
    - New functionality should include unit tests (using mock filesystem
      implementations) and documentation updates.

Contact the maintainer via the repository's issue tracker.


